



Sir
Head Quarters Cambridge 1st April 1776



This Letter will be deliverd you by Jonathan Eddy Esq. the Gentlemen from Nova Scotia who I mentiond to you in mine of the 27th Ulto. He seemd desirous of waiting on the Honorable Congress in Order to lay before them the state of public Affairs, and situation of the Inhabitants of that Province; and as it might be in his power to communicate many things personally, which could not be so well done by Letter, I incouraged him in his design and have advanced him fifty dollars to defrey his ExpencesThe Acadian accompanies him, and as they seem to be solid, judicious Men, I beg leave to recommend them both to the Notice of Congress,1 and am most respectfully Sir Your most obedient humble Servant

Go: Washington

